# ApexGantt ÔÇö AI Coding Rules

You are working with ApexGantt, a JavaScript Gantt / timeline library built on SVG.
Documentation: https://apexcharts.com/docs/apexgantt/
NPM: apexgantt
GitHub: https://github.com/apexcharts/apexgantt

## Framework wrapper detection ÔÇö check `package.json` first

- `react` Ôćĺ use **`react-apexgantt`** instead of the core API.
- `vue` Ôćĺ use **`vue-apexgantt`**.
- `@angular/core` Ôćĺ use **`ngx-apexgantt`**.

Wrappers handle `destroy()` automatically on unmount, accept reactive props, and forward events idiomatically. Use the core API directly only when no framework is detected, or when the user explicitly asks for vanilla.

## Critical Rules

1. **Always call `gantt.render()`** after `new ApexGantt(el, options)`. The constructor builds state but does not paint the DOM.
2. **Always call `gantt.destroy()`** before unmounting in React / Vue / Angular ÔÇö it frees `ResizeObserver`s and global listeners.
3. **`series` is the task array** ÔÇö required. Each task has `id` (unique, stable), `name`, `startTime`, and usually `endTime`.
4. **Date strings must match `inputDateFormat`** (default `'MM-DD-YYYY'`). For ISO dates set `inputDateFormat: 'YYYY-MM-DD'`.
5. **`progress` is 0ÔÇô100**, not 0ÔÇô1.
6. **Milestones omit `endTime`** and use `type: 'milestone'`.
7. **`parentId` must reference an existing task `id`**. Orphans are silently flattened.
8. **Use `updateTask(id, patch)` for single-task changes**, `update(options)` for full reconfigures.
9. **Events fire on the host container element**, not on the gantt instance. Use `container.addEventListener(GanttEvents.ÔÇŽ, ÔÇŽ)`.
10. **`enableSelection: true` is required** for selection APIs and the `selectionChange` event.
11. **Set the license key once** at app startup with `ApexGantt.setLicense('KEY')` to remove the watermark.
12. **Use `parsing` config** instead of manual `.map()` to adapt non-standard data shapes.

---

## Task Data Format

```ts
{
  id: string;                       // REQUIRED, unique, stable
  name: string;                     // REQUIRED, display label
  startTime: string;                // REQUIRED, parsed by inputDateFormat
  endTime?: string;                 // omit for milestones
  progress?: number;                // 0ÔÇô100
  type?: 'task' | 'milestone';      // default 'task'
  parentId?: string;                // hierarchical nesting
  dependency?: string | { taskId: string; type?: 'FS'|'SS'|'FF'|'SF'; lag?: number };
  baseline?: { start: string; end: string };
  barBackgroundColor?: string;
  rowBackgroundColor?: string;
  collapsed?: boolean;
}
```

```js
const gantt = new ApexGantt(document.getElementById('chart'), {
  inputDateFormat: 'YYYY-MM-DD',
  series: [
    { id: 't1', name: 'Design',  startTime: '2026-01-01', endTime: '2026-01-15', progress: 60 },
    { id: 't2', name: 'Develop', startTime: '2026-01-16', endTime: '2026-02-15', progress: 25, dependency: 't1' },
    { id: 'm1', name: 'Launch',  startTime: '2026-02-20', type: 'milestone' }
  ]
});
gantt.render();
```

---

## Lifecycle

```js
import { ApexGantt, GanttEvents } from 'apexgantt';

ApexGantt.setLicense('KEY');                      // optional, once at app startup

const gantt = new ApexGantt(el, {
  series: tasks,
  pixelsPerDay: 25.7,                             // Ôëł week density; omit to auto-fit
  inputDateFormat: 'YYYY-MM-DD',
});
gantt.render();                                   // REQUIRED
gantt.update({ pixelsPerDay: 80 });               // merge + re-render (80 = day density)
gantt.updateTask('t1', { progress: 75 });         // fast single-task patch
gantt.zoomIn(); gantt.zoomOut();                  // raise / lower pixelsPerDay (day Ôćö year)
gantt.destroy();                                  // free observers + DOM
```

---

## API Methods

| Method | Description |
|---|---|
| `render()` | Paint chart. Required. |
| `destroy()` | Tear down. |
| `update(options)` | Merge options & re-render. |
| `updateTask(id, patch)` | Surgical patch. Faster than `update()`. |
| `zoomIn()` / `zoomOut()` | Raise / lower `pixelsPerDay` (continuous zoom). |
| `getSelectedTasks()` | `Task[]`. Needs `enableSelection`. |
| `setSelectedTasks(ids)` | Replace selection. |
| `clearSelection()` | Reset selection. |
| `renderToolbar(container)` | Custom toolbar slot. |
| `isDestroyed()` | Guard. |
| `ApexGantt.setLicense(key)` | Static; call once. |

---

## Events (on container element)

```js
container.addEventListener(GanttEvents.TASK_UPDATE_SUCCESS, (e) => {
  const { taskId, updatedTask } = e.detail;
});
```

| Constant | Event name |
|---|---|
| `TASK_UPDATE` | `taskUpdate` |
| `TASK_VALIDATION_ERROR` | `taskValidationError` |
| `TASK_UPDATE_SUCCESS` | `taskUpdateSuccess` |
| `TASK_UPDATE_ERROR` | `taskUpdateError` |
| `TASK_DRAGGED` | `taskDragged` |
| `TASK_RESIZED` | `taskResized` |
| `SELECTION_CHANGE` | `selectionChange` |
| `DEPENDENCY_ARROW_UPDATE` | `dependencyArrowUpdate` |

---

## Pitfalls ÔÇö ÔŁî Wrong vs Ôťů Correct

### 1. Date format mismatch
ÔŁî ISO dates with default `inputDateFormat`:
`{ startTime: '2026-06-01', endTime: '2026-06-15' }` ÔÇö bars don't render.
Ôťů Set the format:
`{ inputDateFormat: 'YYYY-MM-DD', series: [...] }`

### 2. Missing render
ÔŁî `new ApexGantt(el, opts)` ÔÇö nothing paints.
Ôťů `const g = new ApexGantt(el, opts); g.render();`

### 3. React / Vue cleanup
ÔŁî no `destroy()` in unmount ÔÇö observer leak.
Ôťů `useEffect(() => { const g = new ApexGantt(ref.current, opts); g.render(); return () => g.destroy(); }, [])`

### 4. `update()` for one progress change
ÔŁî `gantt.update({ series: tasks.map(...) })` ÔÇö full re-layout.
Ôťů `gantt.updateTask('t3', { progress: 75 })`.

### 5. Milestone with `endTime`
ÔŁî `{ type: 'milestone', startTime: 'X', endTime: 'Y' }` ÔÇö renders as a bar.
Ôťů `{ type: 'milestone', startTime: 'X' }`.

### 6. Listening on the gantt instance
ÔŁî `gantt.addEventListener(...)` ÔÇö `gantt` is not an `EventTarget`.
Ôťů `container.addEventListener(GanttEvents.TASK_DRAGGED, h)`.

### 7. Selection without `enableSelection`
ÔŁî `getSelectedTasks()` returns `[]`.
Ôťů pass `enableSelection: true` in options.

### 8. `progress` as fraction
ÔŁî `progress: 0.75` Ôćĺ 1% bar.
Ôťů `progress: 75`.

### 9. Orphan `parentId`
ÔŁî `parentId` referencing a non-existent id ÔÇö silently flattened.
Ôťů Ensure every `parentId` matches an `id` in the same `series`.

### 10. License key skipped
ÔŁî Watermark in production.
Ôťů `ApexGantt.setLicense('KEY')` once at app startup.

### 11. Direct mutation of `series`
ÔŁî `options.series.push(newTask)` ÔÇö chart doesn't refresh.
Ôťů `gantt.update({ series: [...options.series, newTask] })`.

### 12. Manual data transforms
ÔŁî `tasks.map(t => ({ id: t.task_id, name: t.title, ... }))` boilerplate.
Ôťů `parsing: { id: 'task_id', name: 'title', startTime: 'start_date', endTime: 'end_date' }`.

---

## Framework Wrappers

```bash
npm install react-apexgantt   # React
npm install vue-apexgantt     # Vue 3
npm install ngx-apexgantt     # Angular
```

All wrappers call `destroy()` automatically on unmount and forward typed events from `GanttEventMap`.
